The major road agencies will be accommodated in a Sh2.9 billion office complex being put up on nine acres in Embakasi. The building is being put up near Jomo Kenyatta International Airport, opposite the Kenya Civil Aviation Authority headquarters. “The proposed office complex will host employees of Kenya Urban Roads Authority, Kenya National Highways Authority, Kenya Rural Roads Authority, Kenya Road Boards,National Construction Authority and Engineers Board of Kenya,” Kenha director general Peter Mundinia said during a visit to the building on Monday. Construction began on March 13 and is set to be completed in 2019. It is currently at the second phase. Construction is being done by the China National Aero-Technology International Engineering Corporation and is funded jointly by the World Bank and the Kenyan government. Mundinia said the project is part of the Vision 2030 blueprint.  